            <h2>About Sahil Swain</h2>
            <p>Sahil is of Indian origin, and it means ‘leader.’ Although the word originally
                referred to a beach or shoreline, it has evolved to denote someone who directs similarly to the sea. <br>
                In many cultures, the name Sahil is given to a person who guides or leads a communit
                y. Hence, the sea or shoreline is a great inspiration for the name.</p>
